The paper discusses a methodology for engineering trustworthy self-adaptive software, which involves design-time and runtime modelling and verification, as well as industry-adopted assurance processes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dynamic assurance cases, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions the application of the methodology to embedded and service-based systems, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
